data.text:
Country music's hottest start Zach Bryan is heading to Houston, Texas at the end of July 2024 for a huge concert. Zach's popularity has soared so much that he is selling out stadiums.

Lat year, he sold out the Superdome in New Orleans, Louisiana and now he is set to perform inside NRG Stadium in Houston, Texas on Saturday, July 27th, 2024. This show is going to be huge and you're not gonna wanna miss it so don't worry, we got you covered with free tickets!

Zach Bryan is known for hit songs like Something In The Orange, Open The Gate, Burn Burn Burn, and I Remember Everything featuring Kacey Musgraves. Here is the video for the song Something In The Orange.

Zach's show on Saturday, July 27th will also feature Jason Isbell and the 400 Unit, and Levi Turner who will both open up for Zach Bryan. Tickets for the show start at $59.50 and go all the way up to $229.50 for general admission which is located right in front of the stage.

Want to go to the show for free? Gator 99.5 has your tickets for the show. How can win your pair? You MUST download the FREE Gator 99.5 mobile app. Download it here.

You will need the mobile app to send in your entries while you listen to Mike & Scotty in the mornings and Chaz in the afternoons to win your tickets!

So download the Gator 99.5 app right now and get ready to go see Zach Bryan live in concert!
